'''Evan Breeze''' (1798 - 1855) was a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] [[poet]] and [[schoolmaster]]. He used the [[bardic name]] Ieuan Cadfan.

His published works include ''Yr Odlydd Cysurus, cyfaill i'r trallodus yn cynnwys amrywiol ddyriau, cofiant am amrai anwylion…carolau…emynau, etc.'' a volume of religious poems which was published in [[1839 in literature|1839]] by H. Jones, Llanrwst. Breeze also preached at the local [[Wesleyan]] chapel.

He died and was buried in [[Llanerfyl]] in 1855.
<ref>{{cite web|title=Evan Breeze|url=http://wbo.llgc.org.uk/en/s-BREE-EVA-1798.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref>

