'''Piran Gushnasp''', also known by his [[baptized]] name of '''Grigor''', was an [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] commander from the [[House of Mihran]]. In the early 6th century, he was appointed as the new governor (''[[marzban]]'') of [[Sasanian Iberia|Iberia]]. Between 540-542 he converted to [[Christianity]], assuming the Christian name of Grigor. However, this made his family boycott all contact with him, and he was soon executed in 542 at [[Anbar (town)|Peroz-Shapur]] due to [[apostasy]]. A companion of Piran, Yazd-panah, was also executed.

