{{see also|Sharana, Afghanistan|Sharana District}}

'''Sharana''' ([[Kannada]]:ಶರಣ) meaning "to surrender" denotes egoless surrender and refuge in [[Shiva]], the [[Deity]] of [[Hinduism]]. In practice, the word ''sharana'' refers specifically to a person who is a follower (a bhakta or a seeker) of the Lingayat tradition. <ref name="ReferenceA">M. R. Sakhare, History and Philosophy of the Lingayat Religion, Prasaranga, Karnataka University, Dharwad</ref> Sharanas through centuries were responsible for the spread of [[Lingayatism]] in [[India]].

